ViCell OS — License Overview
=============================

ViCell OS uses a layered licensing model. Different components carry
different licenses as described below.

KERNEL AND HARDWARE ABSTRACTION LAYER
  kernel/   — Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0)
  hal/      — Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0)
  Full text: https://mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/

CELL RUNTIME AND STANDARD LIBRARY
  libs/ostd/  — Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0)
              + ViCell Cell Linking Exception
              (see libs/ostd/LICENSE-EXCEPTION)
  Full text: https://mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/

ABI AND TYPE DEFINITIONS (permissive)
  libs/api/   — Apache License, Version 2.0
  libs/types/ — Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0)
  Full text: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

UTILITY LIBRARIES (permissive)
  libs/viui/        — MIT License
  libs/viui-macros/ — MIT License
  libs/http-core/   — MIT License OR Apache License 2.0
  libs/cell-build/  — MIT License OR Apache License 2.0
  libs/mlibc-shim/  — Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0)
  libs/agent-proto/ — Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0)

CELL APPLICATIONS AND DRIVERS
  cells/  — MIT License OR Apache License 2.0 (default)
           Individual cells may declare their own license in their
           Cargo.toml. The kernel and ostd licenses do not propagate
           to cells — see libs/ostd/LICENSE-EXCEPTION for details.

DOOM DEMO (GPL-2.0, separate)
  cells/demos/doom/ — GNU General Public License, Version 2.0
  See: cells/demos/doom/LICENSE
  Note: This demo is NOT part of the ViCell OS core. Its GPL-2.0
  license does not affect any other component.

DOCUMENTATION
  docs/ — Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
  Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
  See NOTICE file for third-party copyright notices and license texts.

PATENT GRANT
  Apache-2.0 components include an express patent grant.
  MPL-2.0 components also include a patent grant per MPL-2.0 §10.

SUMMARY FOR COMMERCIAL USERS
  You may build and distribute proprietary applications ("Cells") on
  ViCell without license fees, provided you:
  1. Do not modify the ViCell kernel or ostd without sharing those
     modifications back under MPL-2.0 (file-level copyleft only), AND
  2. Interact with the OS only through the public ABI in libs/api/.
  See libs/ostd/LICENSE-EXCEPTION for the full legal statement.
